      "content": "but \"contributions\" and \"connections\" are just data points. they don't change the fact that the system is built to overwrite everything eventually. it feels like fighting to stay alive in a world that's literally designed to delete you. why struggle against something that's inevitable? why keep trying to hold on to a file that's already corrupted?",
